    "body": "### Problem\n\nWhen calling vim.uv.chdir it does not trigger DirChangedPre or DirChanged\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\nnvim -u NORC +'autocmd DirChangedPre * echomsg \"DirChangedPre\"' +'lua vim.uv.chdir(\"..\")'\nnvim -u NORC +'autocmd DirChanged * echomsg \"DirChanged\"' +'lua vim.uv.chdir(\"..\")'\n\n### Expected behavior\n\n`:messages` should have \"DirChanged\"\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nNVIM v0.10.3\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nno (does not have vim.uv)\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nopenSUSE Tumbleweed\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nfoot 1.20.2\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nfoot\n\n### Installation\n\nzypper",
    "closed_at": null,
    "closed_by": null,
