            "body": "`vim.uv` (aka `vim.loop`) is low-level, it's almost like FFI. It doesn't \"hook into\" any editor features. We should probably document that.\n\nOTOH, use of `vim.uv` is so common that maybe we need to revisit that assumption. Besides `DirChanged`, I think processes spawned from Lua should be tracked as \"jobs\": https://github.com/neovim/neovim/issues/26861",
