            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "> OTOH, use of vim.uv is so common that maybe we need to revisit that assumption. Besides DirChanged, I think processes spawned from Lua should be tracked as \"jobs\": #26861\n\nI would strongly suggest against that. If we want tighter integration then we need to look to our own higher-level API's: `vim.fs`, `vim.system`.\n\n~Does `DirChanged` work if the user does `:! cd`, if not then I'd argue that it's an unreliable event. Or does that have different behaviour to `vim.uv.chdir()`?~",
